issue fix #30 credit text alignment
Not handling vertical alignment because lilypond doesn't seem to have a way to put a bunch of text at the bottom of pages, other than tagline. Have however handled rights and page numbering if credits contain those associated types etc.

added handling for invisible notes
No longer displaying any notes which are classed as invisible. I.e defined as - <note print-object="no">. Whilst this means lilypond no longer moans about this, we now need to replace them with invisible rests in order to make the bar checks pass.

some work toward issue #41
Started to implement a linked list independently of work on measure. Once this is tested thoroughly and have worked out how to reorganise directions and expressions, this will replace the current note list as it allows for organisation by time, but also a standard pattern for adding space in between notes without a lot of pushing and popping onto a python list.

some work toward issue #41

I'm now thinking tree, because that would also make all of the elements in everything into a proper structure rather than separate entities. This is currently standalone until tested and decision has been made.

Modifications to AttachDirection and AttachExpression methods
Modified Direction and Expression so that new additions: - check their pathway is clear (aka no child in that slot): if it is, add to the current note node - if the pathway isn't clear: check the slot has a value. If it doesn't, replace Nothing with the new node's value - if the pathway isn't clear and the slot does have a value: keep looking for the next slot, starting with that child.
